description:
We are looking for a Maintenance Operations Associate to join our team and help us ensure the efficient and effective operation of our business. The successful candidate will be responsible for managing day-to-day operations, supplies and inventory.



Responsibilities:


* Maintenance experience is required;
* Assist Manager in developing and implementing operational policies and procedures;
* Check mail and packages daily;
* Conduct multiple daily spot checks of hallways, classrooms and staircase for cleanliness and damages and report issues to Operations Manager;
* Clean spills in hallways/classrooms, dust air purifiers, sweep up messes in hall, wipe down desk, sanitize doorknobs, handrails n a daily basis when needed;
* Assist with cleaning classroom trash bins once a day;
* fill copy machines in 301 daily and report any issues with equipment;
* Ability to put chairs and desks together and lift over 60 pounds;
* Identify areas for improvement in operational processes and procedures and discuss with Operations Manager;
* Provide support to other departments as needed;
* Stock inventory;
* Cover operations team members' cleaning duties at CCI and 240 locations when team members are not on site.


**Benefits**


* Health Insurance
* Paid Time Off
* Dental Insurance
* Vision Insurance
* Life Insurance & AD&D
* Short & Long Term Disability
* 403(b) Retirement Plan
* Flexible Spending Account
* Health Savings Account
* Parental Leave
* Employee Assistance Program


Job Type: Full-time



Salary: $35,000 - $37,000 per year
